title: Grateful Dead Live at Gizah Sound and Light Theater on 1978-09-16
lineage: MAC >> Nakamichi CR7a => Korg MR-1000 >> DSF [1-bit 5.6448 MHz Stereo] >> Korg MR-1000 => Korg AudioGate >> WAV [24/96] > flac16
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Good Lovin', Candyman, Looks Like Rain, Row Jimmy, El Paso, Ramble On Rose, Minglewood Blues, Deal

Set 2

Ollin Arrageed*-> Fire On The Mountain-> Iko Iko, I Need A Miracle-> It's All Over Now, Sunrise, Shakedown Street-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around, E: One More Saturday Night

*W Hamza El Din Lunar Eclipse

reviews.review_text:
Nice quality for a audience but...... Love the Shakedown from Giza, its slow and drawn out, very mellow but intense.

The only problem is it a audience that has way to much "audience", lots of talking and bitching by the recording party about the neighbors.

I am sorry but if your recording you need to expect audience participation.

Best Sounding AUD for this show 7October2011
I still have the shn & mp3 files for this show
I downloaded from GDLive years ago and needed some patches.
This seems to be the best sounding AUD available here.
Email me if you have some files for this show or

It was the "space" ... ...nothing else mattered! 5 stars just for that!
Quality This is easily one of the best audience recordings I have ever heard! Gorgeous!
